00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:56.060
CORINA GRIGORAS: Thanks Tom.

00:13:56.060 --> 00:13:57.120
Hi everyone.

00:13:57.120 --> 00:14:00.230
I'm Corina and I'm an
engineer on the Play Console.

00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:02.780
So I'll tell you about
some of the great insights

00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:05.460
you can get from benchmarks.

00:14:05.460 --> 00:14:08.360
Now, as Adam and Tom
mentioned, imagine

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:11.030
you're trying to assess
how your app is doing.

00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:13.850
So go into Play Console,
and you look, for instance,

00:14:13.850 --> 00:14:17.360
at your user acquisition
and your user loss.

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:21.410
If this is what you see, what
do these graphs tell you?

00:14:21.410 --> 00:14:24.210
Well, your user
acquisition is going up,

00:14:24.210 --> 00:14:25.340
so that's good, right?

00:14:25.340 --> 00:14:27.350
That means you're doing well.

00:14:27.350 --> 00:14:29.970
But your user loss
is also going up.

00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:31.470
So what does that mean?

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:33.620
Maybe that's not so good,
because you'd ideally

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:36.980
want to retain users
and not lose them.

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:40.250
This is where benchmarks can
be very useful, because they

00:14:40.250 --> 00:14:42.800
can add context to
these numbers and help

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:45.350
you evaluate these trends.

00:14:45.350 --> 00:14:47.360
Now let's look at
your performance

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:50.780
if we compare it
next to a benchmark.

00:14:50.780 --> 00:14:53.930
In this case, you can see that
your acquisition is not only

00:14:53.930 --> 00:14:56.930
doing well, it's actually
doing really well,

00:14:56.930 --> 00:14:59.180
because your acquisition
is going upwards,

00:14:59.180 --> 00:15:02.150
even though the benchmark
is going downwards.

00:15:02.150 --> 00:15:04.820
This means you're doing
much better in this area.

00:15:04.820 --> 00:15:07.460
So it's a good reason for
you to celebrate and probably

00:15:07.460 --> 00:15:10.910
not invest or focus too much.

00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:14.750
And for user loss, you also
see a positive sign this time,

00:15:14.750 --> 00:15:17.160
because even though
it is going upwards,

00:15:17.160 --> 00:15:20.880
It's doing so at a slower
rate than the benchmark.

00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:23.150
And this is where I find
that benchmarks can give you

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:25.370
really interesting insights.

00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:27.620
What this probably
means is that there

00:15:27.620 --> 00:15:30.800
is limited opportunity in
the market in this area,

00:15:30.800 --> 00:15:32.600
because the trend
that you see, it's

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:34.440
common to the wider market.

00:15:34.440 --> 00:15:38.090
And it's not something
that is specific to Europe.

00:15:38.090 --> 00:15:40.180
So in this example,
you can see how

00:15:40.180 --> 00:15:43.090
benchmarks help you get an
overall positive picture

00:15:43.090 --> 00:15:45.590
of your performance.

00:15:45.590 --> 00:15:48.070
But now, imagine that
your performance is still

00:15:48.070 --> 00:15:50.740
exactly the same, and
the benchmark instead

00:15:50.740 --> 00:15:53.390
look like this.

00:15:53.390 --> 00:15:56.620
In this case, your
acquisition is going upwards,

00:15:56.620 --> 00:15:59.870
but it's doing so at a slower
rate than the benchmark.

00:15:59.870 --> 00:16:03.310
Now the difference might
be pretty tiny today,

00:16:03.310 --> 00:16:07.170
but if this trend continues,
that difference will increase.

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:09.490
So you probably want
to monitor this area

00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:13.030
and start thinking about
how you can address it.

00:16:13.030 --> 00:16:16.960
And this time, your user loss
is actually not doing that well,

00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:19.540
because your user
loss is going upwards,

00:16:19.540 --> 00:16:23.170
but the benchmark is going
downwards in this area.

00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:26.260
This shows that there's a
big opportunity here for you,

00:16:26.260 --> 00:16:29.110
and a lot of headroom
for improvement.

00:16:29.110 --> 00:16:31.120
And this is exactly what
benchmarks highlight

00:16:31.120 --> 00:16:35.320
in these examples, the areas
with opportunity in the market,

00:16:35.320 --> 00:16:37.910
and how large these
opportunities are.

00:16:37.910 --> 00:16:40.600
So it can hopefully help
you prioritize the things

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:43.410
you want to focus on next.

00:16:43.410 --> 00:16:46.450
But there's one
challenge in benchmarks.

00:16:46.450 --> 00:16:49.900
Comparing absolute numbers
of acquisition and loss

00:16:49.900 --> 00:16:54.350
might not always be the right
or the best thing to do.

00:16:54.350 --> 00:16:56.690
To address this
issue, we're also

00:16:56.690 --> 00:16:59.750
working on calculating
change rates.

00:16:59.750 --> 00:17:01.430
Change rates are
relative differences

00:17:01.430 --> 00:17:04.950
of a metric from one
period to the next.

00:17:04.950 --> 00:17:08.690
We will calculate this on all
of the metric configurations

00:17:08.690 --> 00:17:11.250
that Tom mentioned earlier.

00:17:11.250 --> 00:17:14.990
And we will also add benchmarks
to all of these change rates.

00:17:14.990 --> 00:17:17.569
And hopefully, with
all these additions,

00:17:17.569 --> 00:17:20.750
we'll be able to give you better
context on how your app grows

00:17:20.750 --> 00:17:24.020
over time, but also a
meaningful comparison that you

00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:27.550
can use to assess that growth.

00:17:27.550 --> 00:17:29.340
So when all this is
available, here's

00:17:29.340 --> 00:17:32.220
an example of the kind
of insight and analysis

00:17:32.220 --> 00:17:35.490
you'll be able to get
from the Play Console.

00:17:35.490 --> 00:17:38.370
For instance, you'll be able
to compare how quickly you're

00:17:38.370 --> 00:17:41.490
acquiring users, or
you'll be able to check

00:17:41.490 --> 00:17:44.280
if your uninstall rates
are abnormally high,

00:17:44.280 --> 00:17:47.460
or even compare how your
growth performs versus

00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:49.650
the benchmark in
specific countries

00:17:49.650 --> 00:17:50.817
or in some specific devices.

00:17:50.817 --> 00:17:52.733
ADAM CARPENTER: So
